.TH "ata_eh_speed_down" 9 "ata_eh_speed_down" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_eh_speed_down \- record error and speed down if necessary
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" ata_eh_speed_down
.BI "(struct ata_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int eflags "  ","
.BI "unsigned int err_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Failed device
.IP "eflags" 12
mask of ATA_EFLAG_* flags
.IP "err_mask" 12
err_mask of the error

Record error and examine error history to determine whether
adjusting transmission speed is necessary.  It also sets
transmission limits appropriately if such adjustment is
necessary.

LOCKING:
Kernel thread context (may sleep).
.SH "RETURN"
Determined recovery action.
